Description: EN NOIR is a privately held, fashion-forward apparel line.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: EN NOIR is a privately held, fashion-forward apparel line that transforms classic 20th century American sportswear into avant-garde luxury pieces. Using natural fabrics, like lamb, leather and python, EN NOIR’s line of outwear, tops, T-shirts and sweatpants turn practical, and season-less clothing into high-end street wear.  Founder and Head Designer of EN NOIR, Robert Garcia, has been in the fashion industry since 2008. He cut his teeth at the West Coast street wear label Black Scale, was schooled in the legendary Parsons The New School of Design (Tim Gunn of Project Runway) and Otis Parsons. He launched EN NOIR (the French word for “in black”) in 2012.  From its headquarters in Los Angeles, CA, EN NOIR clearly has defined a market for the latest range in exotic natural materials, like bamboo, lamb skin leather and python, to turn the ordinary street wear into the extraordinary.  EN NOIR has established strong following with key celebrities such as Kanye West (who has his own men’s and women’s clothing line), Beyonce (who co-owns the women’s line Dereon), and Kim Kardashian, which have put EN NOIR in the spotlight. Rapper CurT@!n$ emerged as a trendsetter as soon as Kanye West called him a ""fashion genius"" in Complex's 2007 April/May issue. EN NOIR has a co-signed piece by CurT@!n$.  This number of athletes, singers, rappers and personalities wearing EN NOIR or have expressed an interest in the apparel line, include A-listers and fashion icons Rihanna and Jay-Z (who also owns his own fashion line Rocawear). It is not uncommon for celebrities to wear each other’s fashion. The buzz and the ability to stand out in the crowd is what makes fashion successful among pop star, urban artists and those who wish to emulate them – the fans.  The Company is in a number of retail stores including Barney’s of New York, who has agreed to roll-out the EN NOIR merchandise to all its stores globally.
Industry Groups: Clothing and Apparel, Commerce and Shopping, Design

Full Description: Vanguard Atlantic Ltd. has been making private equity investments in American and European high-technology companies since 1985.  The fund is currently closed to new investments other than those that come through our partners or past investments. Their philosophy has been to look for situations where our funds could be leveraged by experience, talent, and a strategic approach to markets.   Although we make other investments, our specialty has been very early stage funding.  We have made  investments in companies that may not yet have been attractive to conventional early-stage venture funds due to under-developed strategic positioning, an incomplete management team, a business plan in progress, insufficient proof of concept, or other characteristics normally required for seed or post-seed investments.  In these situations we have tried to help the founders quickly resolve these difficulties and attract more conventional and continuing financial support.
